            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
                <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm">
                    <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Placeholder Project Three</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">A third project that demonstrates something different or more advanced.</p>
                        <img src="https://picsum.photos/600/300?random=3" class="img-fluid project-img my-3" alt="Project Three">
                        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-primary mt-auto" target="_blank">View on GitHub</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="about" class="about-section py-5" style="background-color: #e8e3df;">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-md-5 text-center mb-4 mb-md-0">
                <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/300x300?text=Your+Photo" class="img-fluid grayscale" alt="Your Photo">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <h2 class="fw-bold mb-4">About Me</h2>
                <p>I'm a passionate developer with experience in building scalable web applications using .NET, Blazor, and other modern technologies. I enjoy solving problems, learning new tools, and bringing ideas to life through code.</p>
                <p>Outside of coding, I'm always exploring new things, working on DIY projects.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="currentOccupation" class="currentOccupation-section py-5" style="background-color: #f4f1ee;">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-10 col-lg-8">
                <h2 class="fw-bold mb-4">Current Occupation</h2>
                <p>
                    I’m currently working as a junior C# developer at Adaro Optics Ltd, a company that primarily offers a glasses subscription service and also processes contact lens orders.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I initially joined the project as a support analyst but soon transitioned into a development role — an exciting next step in my IT career. Although I had no formal training in coding at the time, I embraced the challenge, and with persistence, things gradually started to click.
                    Over the past two years, our team and I have developed a new in-store system for opticians, incorporating technologies such as Radzen, Identity, and microservices.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Today, I contribute to most areas of the project, whether that’s maintaining our legacy Web Forms applications or writing API calls for our warehouse management systems.
                </p>
                <p>
                    My experience in the support role gave me a deep understanding of our databases and business rules, which has proved invaluable in development. I’m often the go-to person when it comes to legacy knowledge and data structure insights.
                    This journey from support to development has been both rewarding and transformative, and I’m excited to continue learning and taking on whatever challenges come next.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="freelance" class="freelance-section py-5" style="background-color: #e8e3df;">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-10 col-lg-8">
                <h2 class="fw-bold mb-4">Freelance Work</h2>
                <p class="text-muted mb-5">Placeholder</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


<section id="contact" class="contact-section py-5" style="background-color: #f4f1ee;">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="fw-bold mb-5 text-center">Contact Me</h2>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <div class="d-flex justify-content-center pt-4">
                    <div style="max-width: 600px; width: 100%;">
                        <EditForm Model="@contactRequest" OnValidSubmit="HandleValidSubmit" FormName="ContactForm">
                            <DataAnnotationsValidator />
                            <ValidationSummary />
                            <div class="p-4">
                                <div class="mb-3">
                                    <label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label>
                                    <InputText id="name" class="form-control" @bind-Value="contactRequest.Name"  />
                                </div>

                                <div class="mb-3">
                                    <label for="email" class="form-label">Email</label>
                                    <InputText id="email" class="form-control" inputmode="email" @bind-Value="contactRequest.Email" />
                                </div>

                                <div class="mb-3">
                                    <label for="message" class="form-label">Message</label>
                                    <InputTextArea id="message" class="form-control" rows="5" @bind-Value="contactRequest.Message" />
                                </div>

                                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send Message</button>

                                @if (isSuccess.HasValue)
                                {
                                    <div class="mt-3 alert @(isSuccess.Value ? "alert-success" : "alert-danger")">
                                        @(isSuccess.Value ? "Message sent successfully!" : "Something went wrong. Please try again.")
                                    </div>
                                }
                            </div>
                        </EditForm>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="text-center mt-4">
                    <div class="d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap gap-3">
                        <!-- LinkedIn Button -->
                        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lewis-paine-2486a3172/"
                           target="_blank"
                           rel="noopener noreferrer"
                           class="btn btn-outline-secondary d-inline-flex align-items-center">
                            <img src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/linkedin/linkedin-original.svg"
                                 alt="LinkedIn"
                                 width="24"
                                 height="24"
                                 class="me-2">
                            Connect on LinkedIn
                        </a>

                        <!-- CV Download Buttons -->
                        <a href="files/lewis-paine-cv.pdf"
                           download
                           class="btn btn-outline-secondary d-inline-flex align-items-center">
                            <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/337/337946.png"
                                 alt="CV PDF"
                                 width="24"
                                 height="24"
                                 class="me-2">
                            Download CV (PDF)
                        </a>

                        <a href="files/lewis-paine-cv.docx"
                           download
                           class="btn btn-outline-secondary d-inline-flex align-items-center">
                            <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/281/281760.png"
                                 alt="CV Word"
                                 width="24"
                                 height="24"
                                 class="me-2">
                            Download CV (Word)
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<footer class="py-3 text-center text-muted" style="background-color: #3a4a4f;">
    <div class="container">
        <small>© 2025 Lewis Paine. All rights reserved.</small>
    </div>
</footer>
